# Objective
  Create source generator ./update_block.py with the rules below.
## Create a Blockly blocks description in json format refer to the target json file.
## Create a nodejs file for Block Register for each json files in the Json Output Path.
## Create a nodejs file that includes functions for Code Generator for each blocks.
## Add the Block into the toolbox.

# conditions
## Block register
  Load json file that describe block info.
  Register it using Blockly.Blocks
## Code Generator
  - Create a function for each blocks and register it using "javascriptGenerator.forBlock"
  - The function
    just print block info and parameters set by user.
## Toolbox
  Add the new catagery for the new blocks.
  The category name is the lastest surffix of the json output file name.

# File Path
## Json file for blocks
  - Target Path: ros2command
  - Target Files: 
    ros2_command_ai_HEAD.json
    ros2_command_ai_ECA.json
  - Output Path: bric_app/src/CustomBlocks/blockJson/{XXX}.js
  - XXX: target file name except extention.
## Block Register
  Output Path: bric_app/src/CustomBlocks/ros2Blocks_{YYY}.js
  YYY: the lastest surffix of the Json output file.
## Toolbox
  Output Path: ./Toolbox/toolboxCustomBasic.js
## Code generator
  Output Path: bric_app/src/Generators/ros2Blocks_{YYY}.js
  YYY: the lastest surffix of the Json output file.

# Special Case
## Active parameter by option
If a parameter has options and each option enables different child parameters:
  - Name definition
    rootParam: selector parameter (ex: task_type)
    options: possible values for rootParam
    childParam: parameter that is active only for a specific option value
  - Block behavior
    Show only active childParams for the selected option of rootParam.
    The order of parameters is in rootParam, options, and childParams.
    Show the description with the options.
    Refer to the condition of each options.
      > Check the 'condition'
        If the condition describe, a condition it should be.
        ex) only when task_type == 5. This option shows only when task_type == 5.
    When rootParam changes, update visible childParams immediately.
    Hide non-active childParams.
    Validate dependent option fields (ex: command_type) based on rootParam.
  - Code generator behavior
    Generate ros2 command with the parameters.
    Do not include hidden/non-active childParams in generated output.
